---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import BackToHome from '../components/BackToHome.astro';
import PageNav from '../components/PageNav.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="What is Money?" pageColor="#00E5FF">
  <Header />

  <main class="main-content">
    <PageHeader title="What is Money?" color="#00E5FF" textColor="#111" />

    <div class="content-container">
      <Breadcrumbs current="What is Money" />
      <p>For something to be money it needs to be good at certain things.</p>
      <p>It should be:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Tough and not easily destroyed.</li>
        <li>Be able to be divided into smaller units so you can buy cheap things easily.</li>
        <li>Easy to carry around.</li>
        <li>Scarce so it holds it's value and buys the same amount of things years later.</li>
        <li>Hard to fake, so you don't have to worry about counterfeits.</li>
      </ul>
      <br />
      <p>If something can do all of the above maybe it can be used as money.</p>
      <p>
        Bitcoin is so good at the above that some people call it <strong class="page-colored-strong"
          >perfect money.</strong>
      </p>
      <BackToHome />
    </div>
    <PageNav />
  </main>

  <style>
    /* Content styles */
    p {
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    ul {
      margin-left: var(--spacing-md);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
